content.thinking:
I found the issue. The `sendCommand` function returns `{ accepted: boolean; commandId?: string; error?: string }`. It does NOT return workspace data. The workspace service does:

```ts
create: async (...) => {
  const result = await sendCommand("createWorkspace", { repository_id: repositoryId, ...options });
  if (!result.accepted) throw new Error(result.error || "Failed to create workspace");
  return result as unknown as Workspace;
}
```

It casts the command ack `{ accepted: true, commandId: "..." }` as `Workspace`! This means `workspace.repository_id` would be `undefined` because the ack doesn't have that field!


So when `expandRepo(workspace.repository_id)` runs, it's passing `undefined`, which means `collapsedRepos.has(undefined)` returns false and the early return prevents any changes. The same issue affects `selectWorkspace(workspace.id)` — the ack probably doesn't include an `id` field either. I need to check what the backend command handler actually returns to understand what data is available.

